co.cask.cdap.api.templates

Interface AdapterPluginRegistry

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AdapterConfigurer, PipelineConfigurer

    @Beta
public interface AdapterPluginRegistry
    This interface provides method to register plugin usage for an adapter. The registered plugins will be available at runtime of the adapter.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • usePlugin

        @Nullable
<T> T usePlugin(String pluginType,
                       String pluginName,
                       String pluginId,
                       PluginProperties properties)
        Adds a Plugin usage to the Adapter and create a new instance. The Plugin will be accessible at execution time via the AdapterContext.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the plugin class
        Parameters:
        pluginType - plugin type name
        pluginName - plugin name
        pluginId - an unique identifier for this usage. The same id is used to get the plugin at execution time.
        properties - properties for the plugin. The same set of properties will be used to instantiate the plugin instance at execution time
        Returns:
        A new instance of the plugin class or null if no plugin was found

        properties - properties for the plugin. The same set of properties will be used to instantiate the plugin instance at execution time
        selector - for selecting which plugin to use
